Dialogue: 0,0:14:24.59,0:14:26.48,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\blur3}然而 在90亿英里外{\r}\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&\blur3}But 9 billion miles away,{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:14:26.70,0:14:29.04,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\blur3}在一个被称为"太阳驻点"的地方{\r}\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&\blur3}at a place called the heliopause,{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:14:29.58,0:14:34.51,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\blur3}太阳风失去动力 几乎没有速度{\r}\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&\blur3}the solar wind runs out of steam and slows to almost nothing.{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:14:36.33,0:14:40.02,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\blur3}在慢下来时 它扭曲太阳磁场成为一道屏障{\r}\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&\blur3}As it slows, it twists the Sun's magnetic field{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:14:40.19,0:14:42.55,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\blur3}抵挡从星际空间而来的{\r}\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&\blur3}into a barrier against cosmic rays{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:14:42.56,0:14:44.24,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\blur3}宇宙射线{\r}\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&\blur3}from interstellar space.{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:14:45.18,0:14:47.41,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\blur3}这个区域被称为"日鞘"{\r}\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&\blur3}This is the heliosheath.{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:14:50.81,0:14:52.37,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\blur3}如果没有日鞘{\r}\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&\blur3}If it wasn't for the heliosheath,{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:14:52.43,0:14:56.52,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\blur3}宇宙射线会一直不停地涌入我们太阳系{\r}\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&\blur3}these cosmic rays would actually pour into our solar system all the time.{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:14:56.94,0:15:00.19,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\blur3}对这些可能影响我们地球{\r}\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&\blur3}The heliosheath acts as a kind of shark cage{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:15:00.58,0:15:02.81,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\blur3}来势汹汹的宇宙射线{\r}\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&\blur3}for these incoming cosmic rays{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:15:02.94,0:15:05.15,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\blur3}日鞘起着鲨鱼笼的作用{\r}\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&\blur3}that might otherwise influence our planet.{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:15:07.44,0:15:08.93,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\blur3}有一些会穿过来{\r}\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&\blur3}Some do come through,{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:15:09.31,0:15:11.79,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\blur3}但不至于象没有这种保护一样{\r}\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&\blur3}but they don't come through as strongly as they would{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:15:11.94,0:15:13.56,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\blur3}来得那么凶猛{\r}\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&\blur3}without that protection.{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:15:16.04,0:15:18.19,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\blur3}人们一向认为{\r}\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&\blur3}It used to be thought that the heliosheath{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:15:18.22,0:15:20.05,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\blur3}日鞘是由磁力垂帘构成的{\r}\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&\blur3}was a rather elegant barrier{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:15:20.06,0:15:22.84,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\blur3}一道简单实用的屏障{\r}\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&\blur3}made of flowing curtains of magnetic force,{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:15:24.22,0:15:25.34,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\blur3}但最近{\r}\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&\blur3}but recently,{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:15:27.56,0:15:30.20,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\blur3}1977年从地球发射的太空船{\r}\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&\blur3}enter Voyager 1 and Voyager 2,,{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:15:31.48,0:15:34.76,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\blur3}旅行者1号和2号进入了该区域{\r}\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&\blur3}probes sent out from Earth in 1977.{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:15:37.42,0:15:39.47,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\blur3}在21世纪早期{\r}\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&\blur3}In the early 21st century,{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:15:39.79,0:15:43.83,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\blur3}这些70年代的设备发回的信息指出{\r}\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&\blur3}these disco-era devices sent back information{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:15:44.08,0:15:47.38,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\blur3}太阳的磁力线{\r}\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&\blur3}indicating that the Sun's magnetic field lines{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:15:47.40,0:15:49.27,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\blur3}不是光滑地连在一起的{\r}\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&\blur3}don't flow smoothly together;{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:15:49.69,0:15:53.77,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\blur3}它们间断开来 成为狂暴的磁泡{\r}\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&\blur3}they break up and reform into violent magnetic froth,{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:15:54.20,0:15:58.73,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\blur3}磁泡里的每一个泡宽一亿英里{\r}\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&\blur3}and each bubble in that froth is 100 million miles wide.{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:15:59.79,0:16:02.51,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\blur3}通常认为 在它们之间是一道光滑 优雅的屏障{\r}\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&\blur3}We used to think that it was a smooth, nice barrier{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:16:02.52,0:16:03.79,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\blur3}但实际上{\r}\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&\blur3}between them, but in fact,{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:16:03.81,0:16:06.62,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\blur3}那是躁动之地 有各种泡和其它形状的图案{\r}\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&\blur3}it's a roiling place with all sorts of bubbles and patterns.{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:16:07.42,0:16:09.45,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\blur3}我想 总有人把宇宙超乎自然地{\r}\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&\blur3}I think there's always been people who think the universe{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:16:09.47,0:16:10.94,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\blur3}进行美化{\r}\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&\blur3}is more elegant than it is{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:16:10.95,0:16:12.87,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\blur3}或是狂暴化{\r}\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&\blur3}and people who think it's more violent than it is,{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:16:13.26,0:16:15.54,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\blur3}以至于我们总会惊讶于一面或其它面{\r}\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&\blur3}and we're always surprised one way or the other.{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:16:15.67,0:16:17.55,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\blur3}而真相是 宇宙有些方面{\r}\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&\blur3}The truth is that some aspects of the universe{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:16:17.58,0:16:19.33,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\blur3}非常美丽 但在别的方面{\r}\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&\blur3}are quite elegant, and in other aspects,{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:16:19.35,0:16:20.81,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\blur3}它非常糟糕{\r}\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&\blur3}it's quite a mess.{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:16:24.28,0:16:27.24,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\blur3}何处是我们银河地区的美丽地方{\r}\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&\blur3}Where are the elegant areas of our galactic neighborhood,{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:16:27.44,0:16:29.14,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\blur3}何处是狂野之地？{\r}\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&\blur3}and where are the rough parts?{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:16:31.66,0:16:35.47,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\blur3}宇宙里的气体和尘埃让我们难以分辨{\r}\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&\blur3}It can be hard to tell with all that gas and dust in the cosmos.{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:16:37.87,0:16:40.51,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\blur3}这有点象从这里看我身后的好莱坞{\r}\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&\blur3}It's sort of like looking here behind me at Hollywood.{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:16:40.52,0:16:41.92,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\blur3}那里有一个标志性建筑{\r}\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&\blur3}There's even a landmark there,{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:16:41.94,0:16:43.45,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\blur3}"神殿唱片"大厦{\r}\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&\blur3}the Capitol Records building.{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:16:43.59,0:16:45.31,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\blur3}你能勉强地看到它{\r}\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&\blur3}You can barely make it out.{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:16:45.55,0:16:46.77,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\blur3}但在更远处{\r}\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&\blur3}And even beyond that,{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:16:46.78,0:16:49.10,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\blur3}山岗就显得很模糊{\r}\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&\blur3}there are some hills that are even hazier.{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:16:49.13,0:16:52.73,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\blur3}这是因为在空气中有东西妨碍了视线{\r}\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&\blur3}It's because there's stuff in the air that blocks the view.{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:16:53.73,0:16:57.34,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\blur3}山岗本身还让我看不了更远{\r}\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&\blur3}The hill itself obscures my ability to look beyond it,{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:16:57.74,0:17:01.98,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\blur3}这有点象非常稠密的分子云中的尘埃{\r}\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&\blur3}and that's kind of like the dust in very dense molecular clouds.{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:17:01.99,0:17:04.94,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\blur3}充斥着尘埃的稠密的分子云构成一堵厚墙{\r}\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&\blur3}When you hit a big wall of a dense molecular cloud{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:17:04.95,0:17:07.01,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\blur3}让你看不到任何东西{\r}\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&\blur3}filled with dust, you can't see anything.{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:17:10.01,0:17:12.67,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\blur3}我们在探索银河地区时{\r}\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&\blur3}When we explore our galactic neighborhood,{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:17:13.41,0:17:16.69,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\blur3}所见依赖于我们怎样去看{\r}\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&\blur3}what we see depends on how we look at things.{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:17:18.05,0:17:21.09,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\blur3}通过观察天空 我们学到一个历史经验{\r}\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&\blur3}One of the things we've learned through the history of looking at the sky{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:17:21.10,0:17:24.03,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\blur3}任何时候 如果用不同方法去观察{\r}\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&\blur3}is that every time you look in a different way,{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:17:24.05,0:17:25.34,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\blur3}你会看到新东西{\r}\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&\blur3}you see new things,{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:17:25.81,0:17:27.69,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\blur3}而用不同方法观察天空{\r}\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&\blur3}and looking at the sky a different way{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:17:27.71,0:17:30.42,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\blur3}简单地说 往往是指{\r}\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&\blur3}often simply means looking in a different part{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:17:30.44,0:17:32.37,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\blur3}使用不同的电磁波频谱{\r}\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&\blur3}of the electromagnetic spectrum.{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:17:32.78,0:17:34.80,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\blur3}当我们用眼睛仰望天空{\r}\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&\blur3}As we look up into the sky with our eyes{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:17:34.81,0:17:36.99,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\blur3}或是借助于光学望远镜{\r}\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&\blur3}or with the aid of optical telescopes,{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:17:37.17,0:17:39.01,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\blur3}所利用的是光谱的可见部分{\r}\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&\blur3}in the visible part of the spectrum,{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:17:39.02,0:17:41.01,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\blur3}我们对着夜空{\r}\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&\blur3}we see the night sky,{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:17:41.03,0:17:42.83,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\blur3}会看到许多的事物{\r}\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&\blur3}and there's a lot to see,{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:17:42.99,0:17:45.31,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\blur3}但这只是其中的一小部分{\r}\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&\blur3}but it's only a fraction of what's out there.{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:17:49.19,0:17:50.77,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\blur3}某些太空望远镜{\r}\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&\blur3}Some space telescopes{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:17:50.78,0:17:54.16,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\blur3}利用红外线成像来穿透宇宙尘埃{\r}\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&\blur3}see through cosmic dust with infrared vision,{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:17:54.73,0:17:58.35,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\blur3}其原理类似于民用红外摄像机{\r}\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&\blur3}similar to that used by commercial infrared cameras.{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:17:59.21,0:18:01.46,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\blur3}我带来了一个塑料袋{\r}\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&\blur3}I've brought with me this plastic bag,{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:18:01.73,0:18:03.98,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\blur3}当我把手放进袋子里{\r}\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&\blur3}and when I put my hand inside of the bag,{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:18:04.73,0:18:06.94,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\blur3}你看不到我竖起了多少个手指{\r}\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&\blur3}you can't see how many fingers I'm holding up.{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:18:08.92,0:18:10.01,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\blur3}利用红外摄像机{\r}\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&\blur3}With the infrared camera,{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:18:10.03,0:18:12.07,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\blur3}你能够看到我身体散发的热量{\r}\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&\blur3}you can see the heat coming off my body,{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:18:12.27,0:18:14.88,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\blur3}我的脸部 比较暖和 呈红白色{\r}\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&\blur3}so my face, which is warm, is red and white,{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:18:15.05,0:18:17.71,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\blur3}但是我的头发 比较低温 明显呈蓝色{\r}\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&\blur3}but my hair, which is cool, shows up as blue.{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:18:18.02,0:18:20.59,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\blur3}因此 利用红外摄像机 你能辩认出{\r}\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&\blur3}So with the infrared camera, you should be able to make out{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:18:20.60,0:18:22.24,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\blur3}我竖起了多少个手指{\r}\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&\blur3}how many fingers I'm holding up,{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:18:22.37,0:18:25.12,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\blur3}哪怕你不能看穿这个塑料袋{\r}\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&\blur3}even though you can't see through this bag.{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:18:26.14,0:18:28.73,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\blur3}这就是天文学家为什么能穿透宇宙尘埃{\r}\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&\blur3}That's how astronomers peer through cosmic dust{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:18:28.74,0:18:31.41,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\blur3}去观察隐藏在视线之后的事物{\r}\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&\blur3}when they want to see things that are hidden from sight.{\r}
