Dialogue: 0,0:28:22.97,0:28:25.51,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\blur3}它被认为是三合星{\r}\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&\blur3}it turned out to be a triple system.{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:28:26.69,0:28:29.97,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\blur3}阿尔法A星是典型的类太阳恒星{\r}\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&\blur3}Alpha Centauri A is very much a sun-like star,{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:28:30.08,0:28:32.58,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\blur3}其质量几乎与太阳相当{\r}\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&\blur3}nearly exactly the same mass as our Sun.{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:28:33.08,0:28:35.95,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\blur3}阿尔法B星则稍小一些{\r}\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&\blur3}Alpha Centauri B is a little bit less massive.{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:28:37.08,0:28:39.51,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\blur3}第三颗星 比邻星{\r}\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&\blur3}The third star, Proxima Centauri,{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:28:39.86,0:28:41.27,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\blur3}是一颗M型恒星{\r}\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&\blur3}is an M-type star.{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:28:41.30,0:28:43.00,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\blur3}质量非常小{\r}\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&\blur3}It's a very low-mass star,{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:28:43.13,0:28:46.09,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\blur3}或许只有太阳的12%{\r}\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&\blur3}having perhaps only 12% the mass of our Sun.{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:28:46.37,0:28:49.72,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\blur3}它非常微弱 肉眼看不到{\r}\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&\blur3}It's so faint that we can't see it with our unaided eye.{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:28:52.50,0:28:55.33,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\blur3}其它非常出名的恒星邻居{\r}\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&\blur3}It turns out that other very well-known neighbor stars{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:28:55.35,0:28:57.58,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\blur3}结果也都是双星{\r}\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&\blur3}are also multiple systems.{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:28:59.94,0:29:02.88,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\blur3}天狼星 距离我们8.6光年{\r}\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&\blur3}Sirius, just 8.6 light-years away{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:29:03.12,0:29:04.86,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\blur3}在数千年里{\r}\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&\blur3}and famed for thousands of years{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:29:04.88,0:29:07.41,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\blur3}一直以天空里最亮的星而著名{\r}\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&\blur3}as the brightest single star in the sky,{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:29:08.18,0:29:10.37,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\blur3}是一颗双星{\r}\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&\blur3}is really a binary star.{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:29:11.09,0:29:14.37,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\blur3}大多数恒星的质量和体积比太阳小{\r}\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&\blur3}Most stars are less massive and smaller than our Sun,{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:29:14.54,0:29:16.91,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\blur3}同时 大多数恒星是双星系统{\r}\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&\blur3}and most stars are in binary systems.{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:29:17.13,0:29:20.38,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\blur3}从这两方面来看 太阳稍为有点例外{\r}\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&\blur3}In both respects, our Sun is a little bit of an exception.{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:29:23.52,0:29:26.81,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\blur3}大多数恒星是红矮星或褐矮星{\r}\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&\blur3}The majority of stars are red dwarfs or brown dwarfs.{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:29:27.94,0:29:30.58,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\blur3}红矮星占恒星数量的70%{\r}\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&\blur3}Red dwarfs make up 70% of the stars{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:29:30.67,0:29:33.05,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\blur3}不单在我们银河是这样 在宇宙里也是如此{\r}\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&\blur3}not only in our galaxy but in the universe,{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:29:33.36,0:29:35.76,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\blur3}因此 即使是我们围绕太阳运行{\r}\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&\blur3}and so even though we orbit our Sun{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:29:35.77,0:29:38.91,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\blur3}我们倾向于说它是神圣的恒星{\r}\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&\blur3}and we tend to think of it as the iconic star,{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:29:39.30,0:29:41.70,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\blur3}但事实上 这种红矮星非常普遍{\r}\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&\blur3}really, the red dwarfs are far more common.{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:29:42.88,0:29:44.72,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\blur3}对于褐矮星这些邻居{\r}\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&\blur3}As for the brown dwarfs,{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:29:45.23,0:29:47.33,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\blur3}我们在20世纪90年代之前{\r}\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&\blur3}these are neighbors we weren't sure existed{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:29:47.34,0:29:49.13,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\blur3}还不能肯定它们的存在{\r}\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&\blur3}until the 1990s.{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:29:49.91,0:29:53.22,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\blur3}它们不太象恒星 但它们不是行星{\r}\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&\blur3}They're not quite stars, but they're not planets.{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:29:54.20,0:29:57.01,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\blur3}噢 而且它们不是真的褐色{\r}\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&\blur3}Oh, and they're not really brown either.{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:29:57.92,0:30:02.08,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\blur3}褐矮星是我们太阳系最神秘的居民之一{\r}\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&\blur3}The brown dwarfs are some of the most mysterious denizens of the solar neighborhood{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:30:02.41,0:30:05.79,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\blur3}因为它们非常非常寒冷 所以非常黑{\r}\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&\blur3}because they're really very, very cold, and they're very dark,{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:30:05.80,0:30:08.19,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\blur3}这就意味着不能发出大量的光{\r}\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&\blur3}and that means that they don't give off a lot of light,{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:30:08.41,0:30:10.17,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\blur3}因此它们非常难以看到{\r}\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&\blur3}and they're very difficult to see.{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:30:12.72,0:30:16.22,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\blur3}2011年 美国宇航局一架广角红外探测器{\r}\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&\blur3}In 2011, one of NASA's space telescopes,{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:30:16.81,0:30:20.97,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\blur3}即简称WISE的太空望远镜{\r}\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&\blur3}the Wide-Field Infrared Survey Explorer, or WISE,{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:30:21.49,0:30:24.97,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\blur3}发现了恰好位于我们地区的一系列褐矮星{\r}\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&\blur3}found a series of brown dwarfs right in our neighborhood,{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:30:25.26,0:30:27.82,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\blur3}它们距离我们在9至40光年之间{\r}\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&\blur3}between 9 and 40 light-years away,{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:30:28.15,0:30:31.40,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\blur3}拥有我们曾认为不可能的表面温度{\r}\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&\blur3}with surface temperatures once considered impossible.{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:30:32.69,0:30:36.58,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\blur3}我们发现的这些褐矮星 其中有一颗很清凉{\r}\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&\blur3}One of these brown dwarfs that we found is actually so cool{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:30:36.77,0:30:38.24,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\blur3}你可以用手去触摸它{\r}\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&\blur3}that you could touch it with your hand.{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:30:38.25,0:30:40.19,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\blur3}它只有华氏80度（约27摄氏度）{\r}\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&\blur3}It's only 80 degrees Fahrenheit,{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:30:40.34,0:30:43.30,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\blur3}同样的温度在地球这里 会是好天气{\r}\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&\blur3}the same temperature as a really lovely day out here on Earth.{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:30:43.78,0:30:46.03,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\blur3}因此 以后的发现谁也说不清楚{\r}\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&\blur3}And so who knows what else we'll find.{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:30:46.70,0:30:49.13,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\blur3}我们观察得越多 发现就越多{\r}\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&\blur3}The more we look, the more we see.{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:30:51.20,0:30:53.84,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\blur3}为什么恒星的颜色不尽相同？{\r}\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&\blur3}Why are stars so many different colors?{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:30:54.37,0:30:57.35,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\blur3}这是路易斯安那州巴吞鲁日的安娜.K{\r}\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&\blur3}That's what Anna K. of Baton Rouge, Louisiana,{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:30:57.38,0:30:59.88,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\blur3}写信给《宇宙》咨询的问题{\r}\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&\blur3}texted to ask The Universe.{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:31:00.98,0:31:03.23,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\blur3}安娜 这问题很有趣{\r}\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&\blur3}Anna, that's a really interesting question.{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:31:03.77,0:31:06.23,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\blur3}总的来说 恒星颜色不尽相同{\r}\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&\blur3}Basically, stars have slightly different colors{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:31:06.24,0:31:08.59,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\blur3}是因为其表面温度不同{\r}\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&\blur3}because they have different surface temperatures.{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:31:09.19,0:31:12.23,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\blur3}温度不高的恒星 例如参宿四 看起来是淡红色{\r}\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&\blur3}Cool stars like Betelgeuse look reddish,{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:31:12.30,0:31:15.58,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\blur3}它们只有华氏6 000 7 000度（约摄氏3 300至3 900度）{\r}\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&\blur3}and they have temperatures of only 6,000 or 7,000 degrees Fahrenheit.{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:31:16.35,0:31:19.52,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\blur3}最热的恒星 比如参宿七 呈浅蓝色{\r}\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&\blur3}The hottest stars, like Rigel, appear bluish,{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:31:19.65,0:31:22.06,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\blur3}它们的温度超过了20 000度（约摄氏11 000度）{\r}\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&\blur3}and they're upwards of 20,000 degrees.{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:31:22.52,0:31:24.08,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\blur3}至于太阳这样的恒星{\r}\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&\blur3}Then there are stars like the Sun,{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:31:24.17,0:31:26.71,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\blur3}温度为10 000 11 000度（约摄氏5 500至6 100度）{\r}\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&\blur3}with temperatures of 10,000 or 11,000 degrees,{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:31:26.73,0:31:28.04,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\blur3}看起来是白色的{\r}\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&\blur3}and they look white.{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:31:28.38,0:31:30.88,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\blur3}现在 初升的太阳看起来是黄色{\r}\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&\blur3}Now, the Sun looks yellow when it's setting,{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:31:30.90,0:31:32.98,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\blur3}这是因为大气层的影响{\r}\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&\blur3}but that's because of atmospheric effects.{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:31:32.99,0:31:34.81,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\blur3}它真正的颜色是白色{\r}\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&\blur3}Its true color is white.{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:31:38.96,0:31:41.23,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\blur3}那里不是只有恒星{\r}\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&\blur3}There are more than stars out there.{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:31:41.96,0:31:44.45,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\blur3}我们在本地泡的里面和外面发现了{\r}\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&\blur3}We've discovered hundreds of neighboring planets{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:31:44.46,0:31:47.02,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\blur3}数以百计的行星邻居{\r}\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&\blur3}inside and outside the local bubble.{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:31:47.81,0:31:51.01,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\blur3}我们通过开普勒任务 已经发现了{\r}\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&\blur3}We have discovered a lot of exoplanet candidates{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:31:51.20,0:31:52.76,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\blur3}大量申报中的外星球{\r}\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&\blur3}through a mission called Kepler{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:31:52.84,0:31:56.21,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\blur3}该任务利用行星经过其母恒星面前时{\r}\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&\blur3}that is looking at essentially little eclipses,{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:31:56.49,0:31:58.92,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\blur3}光线变弱少许接着复原{\r}\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&\blur3}when a planet moves in front of its parent star{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:31:58.94,0:32:00.05,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\blur3}这一原理{\r}\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&\blur3}and then out,{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:32:00.06,0:32:02.73,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\blur3}去观察星光的微弱变化{\r}\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&\blur3}and the light dips a little and then goes back up.{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:32:03.77,0:32:05.39,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\blur3}它非常难以看到{\r}\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&\blur3}It's very difficult to see,{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:32:05.64,0:32:09.92,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\blur3}类似于在拉斯维加斯大道上 去寻找唯一一盏熄灭了的灯{\r}\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&\blur3}analogous to watching for a single lightbulb going out on the Vegas Strip.{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:32:10.09,0:32:11.56,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\blur3}但开普勒{\r}\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&\blur3}But Kepler is capable{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:32:11.58,0:32:13.66,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\blur3}是十分精确的测量高手{\r}\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&\blur3}of doing these measurements so precisely{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:32:13.89,0:32:16.09,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\blur3}它能在象我们太阳一样的恒星周围{\r}\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&\blur3}that it's able to find even planets{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:32:16.12,0:32:19.13,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\blur3}发现环绕运行的行星 即使它象地球那样小{\r}\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&\blur3}as small as our own Earth around stars like our Sun.{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:32:21.92,0:32:24.85,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\blur3}我们发现第一颗外星球只有15年{\r}\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&\blur3}The first exoplanet we discovered was only about 15 years ago{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:32:24.87,0:32:27.53,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\blur3}这很类似于我们是大街上唯一的房子{\r}\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&\blur3}and it was very much like we were the only house on the block,{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:32:27.55,0:32:30.13,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\blur3}然后我们看到第一个邻居建房子{\r}\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&\blur3}and we saw the first neighbor putting up their house,{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:32:30.26,0:32:32.94,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\blur3}从此之后 街区全面发展壮大{\r}\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&\blur3}and ever since then, the entire neighborhood has grown.{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:32:32.95,0:32:36.27,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\blur3}外星球群落就这样在我们本地建起来了{\r}\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&\blur3}You built up communities of other exoplanets out in our local neighborhood.{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:32:39.80,0:32:41.20,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\blur3}据我们所知{\r}\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&\blur3}As far as we know,{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:32:41.63,0:32:44.77,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\blur3}外太阳系最靠近我们的行星邻居{\r}\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&\blur3}our nearest planetary neighbor outside the solar system{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:32:44.78,0:32:48.98,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\blur3}来到了大街上 距离我们10.5光年{\r}\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&\blur3}is just down the street, 10.5 light-years away,{\r}
